notes.body_html:
Hello Manisha,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regards to your order #656362065710878720-54312, as checked due to some unforeseen circumstances, the order was not delivered to you by the expected date of delivery. Please accept my apologies for the same.

As per the records, your order is delivered to you on 14th December 2025. We have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. 

We look forward to having an opportunity to serve you in the future.

We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.

For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section. 

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards,
PharmEasy

notes.body_html:
Hello Sahil,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
I understand your query is about the refund of your medicine order #653564815121031168-41097.
 
Upon checking, I see that the refund of Rs.1853.63/- has been completed on 04th December 2025 from our end. The refund amount is credited to your payment source successfully. 
 
For better clarification kindly contact your bank customer service with ARN 533338434221.

If still you b=have not received the refund we request you to raise a chrgeback in your bank. For an SBI UPI chargeback via the Paytm app (or any app), you first use the app's "Raise a Dispute" feature with your UPI ID & Transaction ID, then contact your bank (SBI), and escalate to NPCI if unresolved. NCPI Link: https://www.npci.org.in/upi-complaint

1. Go to your transaction history. Find the problematic SBI UPI transaction. Select the transaction and choose "Raise a Dispute," "Report an Issue," or similar option. Provide details like the Transaction ID, amount, date, and a clear description of the issue.

2. Contact SBI (Your Bank): Immediately inform State Bank of India about the transaction error. Provide your UPI ID, Transaction ID, and the exact time/date.

3. Escalate to NPCI (If Needed): If your bank or Paytm doesn't resolve it, use the NPCI's Dispute Redressal System. You'll need the UPI Transaction ID (a 12-digit reference number) for this.
 
If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels, on the App or website, listed in the "Need Help" section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

notes.body:
Dear Team PharmEasy,

Thank you for your response. Honestly, this reply looks more like a joke
than a resolution.

You have mentioned that the order was delivered to me on 13th December
2025. Let me clarify the reality:
I personally contacted your courier partner’s office and collected the
medicines myself. This was done only because my parents’ health was
continuously degrading, and I could not afford to wait any longer for your
so-called delivery process.

So please do not claim this as a successful delivery by PharmEasy.

From your end, there was:

No proper delivery

No callback from any senior executive, despite my call to customer support
on 12th December

No coordination with the delivery agent

Only repeated, copy-paste responses


Is this what PharmEasy calls customer service for essential medicines?
It clearly appears that you are only concerned about earning money, not
about customers or their medical emergencies.

Marking this ticket as “resolved” without actually resolving the issue is
completely unacceptable. I will be sharing my entire experience on social
media platforms and will also proceed with filing a formal complaint in the
Labour Court due to negligence in an essential service.

If this is not a joke, then I seriously question your service standards.

Do not close this ticket without a proper acknowledgment of failure and
accountability.

Regards,
Keshav Deo
Call only on :- 9113468578

notes.body: Hello Saurab,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with regards to your order #658134361012482048-95118, we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.     As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the SIMILAC PLUS INFANT FORMULA WITH ADDED DHA & VITAMIN E STAGE 1 400GM TIN (UPTO 6 MONTHS)  on 14th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.     Please note that the medicine will be collected within 24 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 48 business hours. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source account within 7-10 business days.     We appreciate your patience in the meantime.     We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Saurab,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with regards to your order #658134361012482048-95118, we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the SIMILAC PLUS INFANT FORMULA WITH ADDED DHA & VITAMIN E STAGE 1 400GM TIN (UPTO 6 MONTHS)  on 14th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.
 
Please note that the medicine will be collected within 24 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 48 business hours. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source account within 7-10 business days.
 
We appreciate your patience in the meantime.
 
We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

notes.body: Hello Nandakishor,       Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9945998281 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well.      Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps, and I appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.      Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal
notes.body_html:
Hello Nandakishor,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.

Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9945998281 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well. 

Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.

I certainly hope this helps, and I appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile. 

Awaiting your response.

Regards,
Sandhya Nackwal

notes.body: Hello Shushank,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #656896688925212672-98114.      We can see that your order was canceled on 12 December 2025. Due to some unforeseen circumstances and operational issue at our logistic end, the order was not delivered to you by the expected date of delivery. We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.     We have shared the required feedback with the delivery partner and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.     We would like to inform you that cancellation refund of Rs.1971.22 /- initiated on 12th December 2025 and same will be refunded to your source account within 5-7 business days.     We would request you to place a new order and we will ensure the order is delivered to you on priority.     Be rest assured as we have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. Looking forward to delighting you soon.     If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Shushank,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #656896688925212672-98114. 
 
We can see that your order was canceled on 12 December 2025. Due to some unforeseen circumstances and operational issue at our logistic end, the order was not delivered to you by the expected date of delivery. We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

We have shared the required feedback with the delivery partner and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.
 
We would like to inform you that cancellation refund of Rs.1971.22 /- initiated on 12th December 2025 and same will be refunded to your source account within 5-7 business days.
 
We would request you to place a new order and we will ensure the order is delivered to you on priority.
 
Be rest assured as we have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. Looking forward to delighting you soon.
 
If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

Dear PharmEasy Team,

I am writing to express my serious concern and disappointment regarding the
handling of my recent order (Order ID: 656317517474824192). This issue is
completely unacceptable, especially considering that the order contains
medicines, not regular goods.

On 10th December, the delivery agent called me and asked me to come to
Bihpur Chowk, which is around 3 km away from my home. When I refused, he
assured me that the order would be delivered the next day, i.e., 11th
December. However, I did not receive the order on that day.

I contacted Customer Support on 11th itself and was informed that a
complaint had been registered. Today, 12th December, I received an “Out for
Delivery” message, yet the order still has not been delivered. I called
today to customer support but I didn't get any resolution.

This raises a serious question—what kind of service is this? Have I made a
mistake by purchasing medicines from your platform? I need an immediate and
proper resolution to this issue. Otherwise, I will be compelled to escalate
this matter further, including sharing the experience on social media
platforms.

I have been purchasing medicines from PharmEasy for the past five years,
and I expect better service. Even last year, I had faced a similar issue
and had to collect the package from your  courier office. This time, I will
not tolerate such negligence.

Kindly treat this matter with the highest priority and provide a prompt
resolution.

Regards,
Keshav Deo

I am writing to express my serious concern and disappointment regarding the handling of my recent order (Order ID: 656317517474824192). This issue is completely unacceptable, especially considering that the order contains medicines, not regular goods.

On 10th December, the delivery agent called me and asked me to come to Bihpur Chowk, which is around 3 km away from my home. When I refused, he assured me that the order would be delivered the next day, i.e., 11th December. However, I did not receive the order on that day.

I contacted Customer Support on 11th itself and was informed that a complaint had been registered. Today, 12th December, I received an “Out for Delivery” message, yet the order still has not been delivered. I called today to customer support but I didn't get any resolution.

This raises a serious question—what kind of service is this? Have I made a mistake by purchasing medicines from your platform? I need an immediate and proper resolution to this issue. I have been purchasing medicines from PharmEasy for the past five years, and I expect better service. Even last year, I had faced a similar issue and had to collect the package from your  courier office. This time, I will not tolerate such negligence.

Kindly treat this matter with the highest priority and provide a prompt resolution.

Regards,
Keshav Deo
Mob:- 9113468578

notes.body: Hello Ashfaq,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with regards to your order #657411854489686016-44836, we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.     As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the TYNOR CERVICAL COLLAR SOFT WITH CHIN SIZE MEDIUM 1  on 16th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.     Please note that the medicine will be collected within 48 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 5 business days. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source within 7-10 business days.     We appreciate your patience in the meantime.     We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Ashfaq,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with regards to your order #657411854489686016-44836, we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the TYNOR CERVICAL COLLAR SOFT WITH CHIN SIZE MEDIUM 1  on 16th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.
 
Please note that the medicine will be collected within 48 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 5 business days. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source within 7-10 business days.
 
We appreciate your patience in the meantime.
 
We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy
